This paper deals with wireless transmission over fading channels powered by energy harvesting and storage devices. It involves optimization of power control strategy to maximize the long-term time-averaged transmission rate under battery operational constraints for energy harvesting. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their information processing capabilities. 

The paper also involves the design of an online power control solution, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with the design and analysis of communication networks and protocols. 

The use of Lyapunov optimization techniques to design the online power control solution makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and design of control systems. 

The paper also involves the characterization of the performance bound of the proposed algorithm, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.MA (Machine Learning), which deals with the study of algorithms and models that enable machines to learn from data. 

Finally, the simulation results demonstrate a significant performance gain of the proposed algorithm over alternative online approaches, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the study of algorithms and models that enable machines to learn from data.
